description: Provides table of gendered and gender-neutral reciprocal relationships for various relationship types (ie. Father-Son, Father-Daughter, Father-Child)

fields.description: Indicates if this reciprocal lookup is active.
fields.inlineHelpText: Indicates if this reciprocal lookup is active.
fields.label: Active

fields.description: The value used for the Reciprocal Setting if the Contact's Gender or Salutation field indicates Female gender.
fields.inlineHelpText: The value used if the Contact's gender field matches the values in the Female Custom Label or the Contact's Salutation indicates gender.
fields.label: Female

fields.description: The value used for the Reciprocal Setting if the Contact's Gender or Salutation field indicates Male gender.
fields.inlineHelpText: The value used if the Contact's gender field matches the values in the Male Custom Label or the Contact's Salutation indicates gender.
fields.label: Male

fields.description: The value used if the Contact's Gender and Saluation fields don't indicate gender.
fields.inlineHelpText: The value used if the Contact's gender field does not match either the Male or Female Custom Labels, and the Contact's Salutation does not infer gender.
fields.label: Neutral
